# Regional language (authoritative)

## App languages

- **Default UI language:** `ar` (`APP_DEFAULT_LANGUAGE` in `app-branding.config.ts`)
- **Secondary UI language:** `en`

Use helpers in `src/app/core/utils/regional-language.util.ts` and `LocalStorageService` wrappers ‚Äî do not reimplement.

---

## Save (`Is_Regional` / API input)

When **creating or updating** user-entered bilingual content:

| UI language | `Is_Regional` |
|-------------|---------------|
| Arabic (`ar`) | `false` |
| English (`en`) or any non-`ar` | `true` |

```ts
isRegional: this.localStorageService.isRegionalApiInput()
// isRegionalApiInput(lang) => lang !== 'ar'
```

**Never** bind `Is_Regional` to a manual checkbox unless the feature explicitly requires it.

---

## Display ‚Äî two ERP field conventions

Do **not** use one rule for every field. There are **two** conventions:

### 1. Reference / lookup data (statuses, types, categories, workflow status names)

ERP convention: **`Name` = English**, **`Name_Regional` = Arabic**.

```ts
this.localStorageService.pickLocalizedField(
  String(item.Name || ''),
  String(item.Name_Regional || ''),
)
// Arabic UI ‚Üí Name_Regional; English UI ‚Üí Name
```

### 2. User-entered donation request content (`Title`, `Description`, `Address`, ‚Ä¶)

ERP convention: **`Title` = Arabic**, **`Title_Regional` = English** (matches save: EN ‚Üí `Is_Regional = true`).

```ts
this.localStorageService.pickRequestContentField(
  String(raw.Title || ''),
  String(raw.Title_Regional || ''),
)
// Arabic UI ‚Üí Title; English UI ‚Üí Title_Regional
```

Use **`pickRequestContentField`** (in `regional-language.util.ts` / `LocalStorageService`) ‚Äî not manual `if (isArabicUi)` blocks and not `pickLocalizedField`.

---

## Save vs display

| Concern | Use |
|---------|-----|
| Save / API write | `isRegionalApiInput()` |
| Reference labels | `pickLocalizedField(Name, Name_Regional)` |
| Request title/description/address | Explicit AR‚Üídefault, EN‚Üí`*_Regional` (convention **2**) |

Never invert or reuse save logic for display.

---

## Language change

- Keep **raw** API objects (`rawDetails`, list rows, lookup arrays).
- On `LanguageDirService.userLanguageCode$`, **rebuild displayed labels** from raw data ‚Äî do not reload the API unless only one language was returned.
- See **`regional-data-remapping`** for component structure.
